r_2
\frac{d^2\psi}{dx^2}+k\psi=0
k=\frac{2mE}{\hbar^2}
a\psi''(x)+b\psi'(x)+c\psi(x)=0
ar^2+br+c=0
r^2+k=0
r=\pm \sqrt{k}
\psi(x)=\exp\left(\sqrt{\frac{2mE}{\hbar^2}}x\right)+\exp\left(-\sqrt{\frac{2mE}{\hbar^2}}x\right)
\psi(x)=A\sin kx+B\cos kx
r=\pm \sqrt{-k}
\psi(x)=a\exp\left(\sqrt{k}ix\right)+b\exp\left(-\sqrt{k}ix\right)
\psi(x)=A\sin \sqrt{k}x+B\cos \sqrt{k}x
r^2+k=0
r=\pm \sqrt{- k}
\sqrt{k} = \omega
 \psi(x) = ae^{i\omega} + be^{-i\omega}
 \psi(x) = a(\cos\omega + i\sin\omega) + b(\cos\omega - i \sin\omega)
 = (a+b)\cos\omega + (a-b)i\sin\omega .
